    "summary": "My name is Sharon Diamant and I have just completed my Astronomy Research Master at Leiden University. During my studies, I have acquired experience in different research fields such as laboratory astrophysics, stellar astrophysics and planetary science at ESTEC/ESA. My experience with these projects have been instrumental to develop a proactive and self-supporting attitude and gave me confidence in my scientific enthusiasm and technical skills. Apart from my studies, I have also worked (remotely due to the COVID-19 pandemic) with Prof. Adam Burgasser and his team at the University of California, San Diego (UCSD) for six months (2020). This internship helped me to extend my (international) network as well as my experience and skills with coding (Python) and working with spectral tools and archives (e.g. The Spex Prism Library). In addition, I work at Luzac college as a tutor and at the Leiden Old Observatory as an educator, tour guide and custodian. These jobs gave me more experience in public speaking and improved my social skills. I have enjoyed my studies, work and other achievements and I am always open to learn new things and to work hard.",
